{{Audio|file=Bluff (Instrumental).mp3|align=center|volume=0.5|secrettext=<span style="font-family:Lancelot">You ready to play?</span>}} __NOTOC__
<div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-first">

<span class="mw-customtoggle-first mw-customtoggle-second"> <div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-second">

<div style="margin:3em; text-align:center; font-family:Girassol; font-size:17px">
[[File:Supersede Barrel2.png|center|380px]]
<span style="font-family:Mansalva">"You know how this game works, right Angel?"</span>

Almost methodically, the first bullet was loaded into the chamber. Even with the rough grip the man had on the gun, it seemed Donnie took pride in loading each round in. His eyes trailed upwards slowly, sitting resting the firearm on the table and pushing it over to Angel. Under the fainting gas lamp and the wide brimmed hat, Donnie kept a glint in his eyes. Was is certainty? Perhaps was it the pride of finally putting down his opponent. It certainly wasn't Angel's first time in the game either.

Donnie was a plump and hideous man, with his gut pushing the table closer to Angel's side as he laughed. It seemed whatever the man did, his stomach would grow larger. It was a trick of the mind, more than likely, but it still felt wrong. There was no pride in himself outside of being alive, perchance. Why else would it go on?

<span style="font-family:Julee">"Of course I do."</span> The bitter taste of blood filled his lips as he watched Donnie load the gun. One round, 5 blanks. It was how the game was always played. 
</div>
</div> </span>

</div>

<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-first">
<div class="mw-customtoggle-first mw-customtoggle-second"> </div>

<div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-third">

<span class="mw-customtoggle-third mw-customtoggle-fourth"> <div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-fourth">

<div style="margin:3em; text-align:center; font-family:Girassol; font-size:17px">
[[File:Supersede Barrel3.png|center|380px]]
<span style="font-family:Julee">"And don't fucking call me that. It's Angelo, you fat fuck."</span>

Angelo took his time to roll the bullet between his fingers, as the transmitter beeped out his pseudo-familiar robotic tone. Donnie only laughed coarsely at the comment, a rough enough grunt between each chortle you fear the next <span style="font-family:Mansalva">"HA"</span> would turn to a coughing fit.

Hell, Angel would rather that. It'd make this whole charade easier. 

As Angelo pushed in the bullet, he glared at Donnie, letting the death in his eyes speak for him. As Don stared back, his laugh faded. There was no humor in their games of chance. Only the spoils of blood and whatever money they kept on the table. Angelo took this game seriously, at least. He already died once when facing him, and Angelo wasn't planning to die again. While his broken jaw meant the rest of his life became a struggle, his grit to step back into the ring had to be impressive.

Maybe a smarter Angelo would have lived with the damaged mouth and moved on from the game, but he had a purpose, and Don was the man standing in the way of that. He wasn't here for money, the weight of Cavallpar rested on the chambered bullets. 
</div>
</div> </span>

</div>

<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-third">
<div class="mw-customtoggle-third mw-customtoggle-fourth"> </div>

<div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-fifth">

<span class="mw-customtoggle-fifth mw-customtoggle-sixth"> <div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-sixth">

<div style="margin:3em; text-align:center; font-family:Girassol; font-size:17px">
[[File:Supersede Barrel4.png|center|380px]]
<span style="font-family:Mansalva">"Still such a priss..."</span>

The dirty grin on Don's face said enough about his opinions, as he took the gun from Angel's hand. His fat fingers freely brushed over the trigger, his familiarity with the firearm kept most others at the table on edge. But, even with the roughness of Donnie's grip, there was still an odd delicacy. A mental pedestal Donnie placed his trusty revolver on. It always worked in his favor, after all. <span style="font-family:Mansalva">"You've still got a lot to learn about this place, and you little plan with the prisoners is a load of horseshit. You're no one's savior."</span> Donnie's smile seemed to only grow, the fancy cigar tilted down as his toothy grip loosened.

<span style="font-family:Julee">"Neither is sitting here and playing roulette."</span> Don rolled his eyes, whirring the chamber around as he looked into it. The dark gray lenses locked onto the live round, and he could barely hide his grin from Angelo as he let it sit.

<span style="font-family:Mansalva">"My point still stands boy, you're not the hero type."</span>
</div>
</div> </span>

</div>

<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-fifth">
<div class="mw-customtoggle-fifth mw-customtoggle-sixth"> </div>

<div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-seventh">

<span class="mw-customtoggle-seventh mw-customtoggle-eighth"> <div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-eighth">

<div style="margin:3em; text-align:center; font-family:Girassol; font-size:17px">
[[File:Supersede Barrel5.png|center|380px]]
<span style="font-family:Julee">"Never claimed to be one."</span>

Angelo and Donnie were two sides of a similar coin. Both were men hunting for answers in the superficial. Chasing the chem-trails of phenomenon as the world they lived in seemed to suffer from it's existence. While Donnie kept his goals close to his chest, Angelo knew he was following the paper trail like so many other groups. Angelo made it more clear what his goals were, which allowed Donnie to try and chip into him through his breathy responses. For now, Angelo only gave the other man silence, loading in another bullet.

<span style="font-family:Mansalva">"In the forever of this universe, you think that this is a new event? Hardly nothing is these days. Just like the ones before us, it'll pass and nothing will be different, Angel."</span> Donnie laughed a little more, squinting steely eyes, trading back the look of violence the other had offered. 
</div>
</div> </span>

</div>

<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-seventh">
<div class="mw-customtoggle-seventh mw-customtoggle-eighth"> </div>

<div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-ninth">

<span class="mw-customtoggle-ninth mw-customtoggle-tenth"> <div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-tenth">

<div style="margin:3em; text-align:center; font-family:Girassol; font-size:17px">
[[File:Supersede Barrel6.png|center|380px]]
<span style="font-family:Julee">"Let's cut the bullshit, yea? I'm tired of this little chat before the round."</span>

When Donnie reached his hand out to grab the gun, Angel picked it up and slammed the handle into the back of the other man's hand. Donnie hissed and pulled his grubby mitts away.

<span style="font-family:Mansalva">"Twat."</span> Donnie spat, the scent of weed rolled across the air, hovering like the fogs of early dawn. Yet he still watched as Angel loaded another round. He could feel the thrill of the hunt in the other's eyes as he slipped a 5th bullet in. Angel quietly ran his hand over the bullets, silently analyzing each of the chambered rounds, then he shifted his attention to the one left. 
</div>
</div> </span>

</div>

<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-ninth">
<div class="mw-customtoggle-ninth mw-customtoggle-tenth"> </div>

<div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-eleventh">

<span class="mw-customtoggle-eleventh mw-customtoggle-twelfth"> <div class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-twelfth">

<div style="margin:3em; text-align:center; font-family:Girassol; font-size:17px">
[[File:Supersede Barrel7.png|center|380px]]
<span style="font-family:Mansalva">"But fine. We can do it your way."</span>

As Angelo set down the gun, Donnie took it from him, alongside the last bullet. His eyes narrowed on the other man, as he tried to slip in the 6th round, pretending it to be a farce. Just like last time, it was Donnie's way of taking back control of the gun. But Angelo corrected him.

<span style="font-family:Julee">"I already put in the live round. Quit your acting and let's play."</span> Donnie grunted in dissatisfaction, forcing in the final round and whirring the weapon's chamber with a flick of his wrist. Lovingly, it was placed on the table, spinning for some seconds before stopping again. Agelo could feel the air tighten as it moved, only a few moments lasted for infinity as they watched where it'd land. Slightly to the right, the gun still pointed clearly towards Don.

For a moment, Angelo watched fear in his eyes. A lack of control, one where he used to manipulate the mechanics to his advantage. But now, they were even. Don picked up the gun, holding it in both hands, then with one. The revolver was then pressed against his own head, and Donnie used his free hand to put out his cigarette. The hiss held itself in the air, counting down the seconds before the trigger was pulled.
</div>
</div> </span>

</div>

