<h2 style="font-family:Sancreek; text-align:center; font-size:30px">Description</h2>
<div style="margin:1.5em; font-family:Girassol; font-size:15px; text-align:left; letter-spacing:1px">
{{Blurimage|file=Level995Image2.png|align=left|width=300px|caption=Cavallpar Saloon.}}
The town of Barstill Creek is a small one, measuring only 30 kilometers at its longest point and consisting of roughly 600 buildings. Due to its night-locked sky, most sources of light within the level remain illuminated, usually requiring the use of gasoline to do so. Akin to many other [[Level List|spaces]], Barstill Creek appears to be fully abandoned, with human habitation implied, but unconfirmed. This lack of population has changed over time as a result of early GOI activities in the level and an entity population that can be managed. The blocked out architecture in the level also suggests intentional planning, with the various structures fitting together with precision. Yet due to the abandoned nature and lack of documentation, further details into the history of the level itself remains unknown. 

Barstill Creek has 102 commercial buildings, about 470 residential buildings<ref>8 of these are governmental buildings</ref>, and 30 industrial buildings repaired. Other buildings across the visual town make the total building count close to 2000. The industrial sect sits on the outskirts of the township, with the commercial and residential section blending together. At the very middle of the village is an exposed space commonly seen as Barstill Creek's town square.

{{Blurimage|file=Level995Image1.png|width=300px|align=right|caption=Aputxer.}}
2.2 kilometers south of the town square is the park. Known to the locals as "Aputxer", many of the plants found here are unique to the town alone. The commonly dry heat of the day mixed in with cold temperatures of the night largely contributed to the overall hostile climate and the uniformed human settlement. Apuxter is 5.5 meters by 7.1 meters, with a gazebo placed at its center and having 4 extruding pathways from it to the park exits. 

In total, Barstill Creek consists of 14 major roadways, with 9 of them going north to south, and the 5 others east to west. There are 10 smaller or otherwise unammed roads and another 23 that are incomplete but still used. The larger roads stand at 3 meters across, and the smaller ones are 1.5 meters. Despite the usual heat of the level, many have claimed the roads to be cool to the touch. This cool feeling extends outwards to many of the building interiors of Level 695, despite a lack of air conditioning or other cooling systems. Among other anomalies, the unusual coolness is attributed to the nearby river, also known as "Riu-gel"

Riu-gel is a large river nearby the southeastern section of Level 695. The water is unnaturally cold, with temperatures reaching 6° Celsius on some measurements. This river is responsible for much of the water pumps and supply within Barstill Creek. The near-freezing water then equalizes with the air, attributing to the cooler temperatures within buildings.
</div>


<h2 style="font-family:Sancreek; text-align:center; font-size:30px">Entities</h2>
<div style="margin:1.5em; font-family:Girassol; font-size:15px; text-align:left; letter-spacing:1px">
{{Blurimage|file=Level995Image3.png|align=left|width=200px|caption=Craufust}}
Beyond the bounds of Barstill Creek, the entity population is unknown, and those who travel beyond the town return with varying reports of entity population. However, within Barstill Creek, poltergheists are known to run about.

The current population within Level 695 have been able to keep the entities from growing too violent, though are still known to play tricks and otherwise lightly injure wanderers for their own humor. Others interact with their enviornment only to support their own wishes, sometimes seen playing with pianos or card across Level 695. Poltergheists are completely invisible to the unaided eye, only taking the form of a white esper when it chooses to be. Capture and removal of the entities is heavy discouraged by the population of Barstill Creek, and may lead to disciplinary action within their judicial system.

The water in Level 695 will sometimes have [[Hydrolitis Plague]]. During this period, the town will clean out all its unused and still water, and Hydrolitis Plague will come through and eat up any corpses or gunk that appears in the river. This weeklong period can be dangerious for those unfamiliar with the cycle, but residents are open to help Wanderers get through it. How this pattern works remains unknown, alongside some of the unique features of the Hydrolitis Plague that makes the cycle possible.
</div>


<h2 style="font-family:Sancreek; text-align:center; font-size:30px">Habitation</h2>
<div style="margin:1.5em; font-family:Girassol; font-size:15px; text-align:left; letter-spacing:1px">
{{Imagebox
|text=<h3 style="font-family:Sancreek; text-align:center; font-size:20px; color:#E4C388">Cavallpar</h3>
The only known population in Level 695. Consisting of nearly 3000 members, Cavallpar habitates both the completed and incompleted residtential buildings. Their language proves difficult for wanderers to interact with, but they have shown willingness to trade supplies and offer temporary housing. According to some, the bulk of Cavallpar's population lives elsewhere. This other residency, known as "Ausoleto" is several dozen kilometers away from Barstill Creek, and requries a week of travel to reach it. Currently, only those born in Cavallpar or are considered to be apart of their population are allowed to go. There is belived to be 6 other bases that Cavallpars do not allow wanderers to freely access.
|file=CalentBackground.png
|inner-style=padding:10px;
}}


{{Imagebox
|text=<h3 style="font-family:Sancreek; text-align:center; font-size:20px; color:#E4C388">Unaffiliated</h3>
The base, nicknamed "Herberts Housing" sits nearby a clifface 1 kilometer upstream from Barstill Creek, and is run by a man named "Herbert Hennesy". They are still looking for new members. The group is rather full of suppliesm, though has not shown an affinity for trading outside of larger scale deals. When asked about Herbert, the residents of Barstill Creek advised against interacting with him.
|file=CalentBackground.png
|inner-style=padding:10px;
}}
</div>


<h2 style="font-family:Sancreek; text-align:center; font-size:30px">Entrances & Exits</h2>
<div style="margin:1.5em; font-family:Girassol; font-size:15px; text-align:left; letter-spacing:1px">
<h3 style="font-family:Sancreek; text-align:center; font-size:20px; color:#E4C388">Entrances</h3>
* Noclipping through projection screens in [[Level 40]] provide a higher likeklyhood of entering Level 695 in comparison to other levels.
* Falling through the beaches in [[Level 397]] will always send wanderers to Level 695.
* Unobsturcted doors in [[Level 627]] may send wanderers to Level 695, among other levels.
* Clipping out of certain windows in [[Level 571]] will provide entry to Level 695, usually via defenestration. Many of the locals don't seem to mind it, oddly.
<h3 style="font-family:Sancreek; text-align:center; font-size:20px; color:#E4C388">Exits</h3>
* Clipping through the side of the canyon has a much higher chance of bringing wanderers to [[Level 192]].
* Unnaturally generating posters in Level 695 can be clipped through and into [[Level 610]].
* Climbing on top of one of the nearby buttes may fade into [[Level 622]].
* Traveling down Riu-gel long enough will lead to entry into [[Level 91]]. This exit is also consistent and reversible, which has lead to easy cross development between the residents of both levels.
</div>
